  "text": "Let T be the 1-dimensional Sym(U)-module where U acts as 0. Write B = Sym(U)#G . Then, if W is any simple G -module, the B-module T ⊗ W is also 1-dimensional and thus simple. Following a construction of Auslander [CITATION_1] , its projective resolution is constructed using the Koszul complex for Sym(V ):",
